18#ifndef _LVM_DEV_CACHE_H
19#define _LVM_DEV_CACHE_H
20
21#include "device.h"
22
23/*
24 * predicate for devices.
25 */
26struct dev_filter {
27 int (*passes_filter) (struct dev_filter * f, struct device * dev);
28 void (*destroy) (struct dev_filter * f);
29 void *private;
30};
31
32/*
33 * The global device cache.
34 */
35struct cmd_context;
36int dev_cache_init(struct cmd_context *cmd);
37void dev_cache_exit(void);
38
39/* Trigger(1) or avoid(0) a scan */
40void dev_cache_scan(int do_scan);
41int dev_cache_has_scanned(void);
42
43int dev_cache_add_dir(const char *path);
44int dev_cache_add_loopfile(const char *path);
45struct device *dev_cache_get(const char *name, struct dev_filter *f);
46
47void dev_set_preferred_name(struct str_list *sl, struct device *dev);
48
49/*
50 * Object for iterating through the cache.
51 */
52struct dev_iter;
53struct dev_iter *dev_iter_create(struct dev_filter *f, int dev_scan);
54void dev_iter_destroy(struct dev_iter *iter);
55struct device *dev_iter_get(struct dev_iter *iter);
56
57#endif
